    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="474"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.852/84: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-19T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >April 19, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:06 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>135. Referring to my despatch No. 10,394 April 11.<note n="5" xml:id="d474fn1"
                        >Not printed.</note> Sale of SS <hi rend="italic">Tine Asmussen</hi>
                    confirmed by W. R. Davis Company as effective yesterday. Terms said by manager
                    Dutch Shell Company as $75,000 one month from date of sale and $150,000 worth of
                    gasoline to be delivered at Houston, Texas. Piatt oil gram price to prevail on
                    date of delivery at Houston. These terms are being checked.</p>
                <p>Finance Minister<note n="6" xml:id="d474fn2">Eduardo Suárez.</note> said purchase
                    has been consummated in accordance with principles international law and facts
                    are being communicated to British and French Governments with view to obtaining
                    their position in the matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
